21/09/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Sulejman Rexhepi, the dean of the Skopje Faculty for Islamic Studies, was elected on Wednesday (20 September) as the new head of the Islamic religious community in Macedonia. 
He easily beat out the other nominee for the post, former Tetovo mufti Muamed Isaini. 
As his main priorities, Rexhepi cited the strengthening of the Islamic religious community and prevention of radical infiltration, as well as the introduction of religious studies in Macedonian schools. 
(A1 TV, Telma TV - 20/09/06)
